        <p>
          When I audit local websites, the hosting is almost never right-sized.
          It's either too cheap to do its job, so the site is slow and quietly
          costing you enquiries, or it's far more than a small business site needs,
          so you're overpaying every month for power you'll never use.
        </p>
        <p>
          Either way, nobody's keeping an eye on it. Hosting is the kind of decision
